# Git Push/Pull via `tmp` Branch

In the `ai-platform-webui` repository, **never push directly to a remote branch matching the local branch name**. Always push to and pull from the remote `tmp` branch.

## Required Commands

```bash
git push origin HEAD:tmp       # push current local branch -> remote tmp
git pull origin tmp            # pull from remote tmp
```

## Forbidden Patterns

```bash
git push -u origin HEAD                        # WRONG
git push origin $(git branch --show-current)   # WRONG
git push -u origin issue/123-feature           # WRONG
git pull origin dev                            # WRONG (for syncing work)
```

## PR Creation

When creating PRs with `gh pr create`, set `--head tmp` since the code lives on the remote `tmp` branch:

```bash
gh pr create --head tmp --base dev ...
```

## Scope

- This rule applies **only to ai-platform-webui**
- Other repositories synced via `/cursor-sync` use standard push/pull conventions
